                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A binding declared as Linear or Ordered in the substructural lattice must be used exactly once. This binding was never used. A Linear binding represents a unique resource that must be consumed; Ordered adds ordering constraints. Check that the binding is referenced exactly once in its scope."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0900",
              "id": "S0900",
              "name": "Linear or Ordered binding never used",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "binding is never used (requires exactly one use)"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A binding declared as Linear or Ordered must be used exactly once. This binding was used multiple times. Linear bindings represent unique resources; Affine bindings may be used at most once; Unrestricted have no constraints."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0901",
              "id": "S0901",
              "name": "Linear or Ordered binding overused",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "binding used more than once (requires exactly one use)"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A linear binding from an outer scope is shadowed by a new let binding with the same name before the outer binding has been consumed (used exactly once). This creates a resource leak: the outer linear binding is no longer accessible within the inner scope and cannot be consumed. Move the outer binding's use before the shadowing let, or use a different name for the inner binding."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0902",
              "id": "S0902",
              "name": "Linear binding leaked via let shadowing",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "linear binding shadowed by let without consumption"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An affine binding may be used at most once, but the analysis detects that it could be consumed in two or more sibling match arms (or if/then/else branches). Although only one branch executes dynamically, the static analysis tracks 'may consume' (not 'must consume'), so this is flagged as a static error. Restructure the code so the affine binding is used in only one branch, or assign it to an unrestricted binding first."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0904",
              "id": "S0904",
              "name": "Affine binding consumed in multiple match arms",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "affine binding may be consumed across sibling branches"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An ordered binding declared in an enclosing scope is used out of declaration order within a handler body. Handler installations impose strict sequential-use constraints on ordered bindings: all uses must respect their declaration order. Reorder the uses in the handler body to match the order in which the bindings were declared."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/S0905",
              "id": "S0905",
              "name": "Ordered binding used out of order within handler",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "ordered resource used out of order across handler"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §1.2, peephole rewrites improve generated code quality. O1500 informs the user when a rewrite fired."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1500",
              "id": "O1500",
              "name": "Peephole rewrite applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "a peephole rewrite fired on the function"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Reserved for a future per-rewrite peephole diagnostic (currently O1500 covers the whole pass)."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1501",
              "id": "O1501",
              "name": "Reserved for future peephole sub-pass",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "reserved diagnostic slot"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Reserved for a future per-rewrite peephole diagnostic."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1502",
              "id": "O1502",
              "name": "Reserved for future peephole sub-pass",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "reserved diagnostic slot"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §2, instruction scheduling exploits ILP within basic blocks by hoisting higher-latency operations earlier."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1503",
              "id": "O1503",
              "name": "Instruction scheduling applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "instruction scheduling reordered independent instructions to hide latency"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §4, modern x86_64 CPUs fuse CMP+Jcc (or TEST+Jcc) pairs into a single µop, but only when both fit within one 16-byte fetch window. This pass aligns such pairs by inserting NOPs as needed."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1504",
              "id": "O1504",
              "name": "Macro-fusion alignment applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CMP+Jcc pair aligned within a 16-byte fetch window for macro fusion"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §5, basic-block-local dead-store elimination removes stores whose effects are immediately overwritten."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1505",
              "id": "O1505",
              "name": "Dead-store elimination applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "stores to memory subsequently overwritten without intervening reads were removed"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §6, picking the shortest legal encoding (32-bit ADD short form, Jcc rel8 over rel32) reduces code size and improves L1i density."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1506",
              "id": "O1506",
              "name": "REX/EVEX prefix tightening applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "instruction shortened to its smallest legal encoding"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §7, branch hints direct the code layout pass to place unlikely branches away from the fall-through path, improving cache density and reducing misprediction penalties."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1507",
              "id": "O1507",
              "name": "Branch-hint code layout applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "unlikely branches moved off fall-through for better code density"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §8, aligning function entries to cache-line boundaries (typically 64 bytes) reduces L1i cache conflicts and improves prefetching efficiency."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1508",
              "id": "O1508",
              "name": "Function-entry alignment applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "function entry aligned to improve L1i cache performance"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §9, constants appearing multiple times in a function are factored into a read-only constant pool, reducing instruction encoding size and improving cache density."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1509",
              "id": "O1509",
              "name": "Constant-pool emission applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "repeated 64-bit immediates factored into a constant pool"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per OS-requirements §6 design-clarification 5: TCO ships in Phase 2 to support the kernel's exception-unwinder path. Capability boundaries, effect-handler installations, and ABI mismatches suppress TCO."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1510",
              "id": "O1510",
              "name": "Tail-call eliminated",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "final call + ret sequence rewritten as a jmp"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per optimization-passes.md §10, loop unrolling replicates loop body by a compile-time constant factor to reduce branch penalties and improve ILP. Phase-2-m9-009 supports only known trip counts with divisible factors; remainder loops are deferred to phase-2-m9-010."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1511",
              "id": "O1511",
              "name": "Loop unrolling applied",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "loop unrolled by explicit factor"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Loop unrolling with #[unroll(n)] requires a known trip count divisible by n. This loop's trip count is symbolic or unknown, preventing safe unrolling. Remainder-loop dispatch to handle unknown trip counts is deferred to phase-2-m9-010. Provide a constant trip count or remove the #[unroll(n)] directive."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/O1512",
              "id": "O1512",
              "name": "Loop unrolling requested on unknown trip count",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "unroll directive ignored due to symbolic or unknown iteration count"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "A symbol is marked as undefined (section_index=0xFFFFFFFF) in the symbol table, but no input PAX exports a symbol with the same BLAKE3 name hash. The linker cannot resolve this reference."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/B1700",
              "id": "B1700",
              "name": "Undefined symbol",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "undefined symbol — no exporting PAX provides it"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An ImportsSection entry requests a capability (by BLAKE3 name hash), but no PAX's ExportsSection provides a capability with that hash. The linker cannot bind this required capability."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/B1701",
              "id": "B1701",
              "name": "Unbound capability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "unbound capability — no export matches an import"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Per OS-requirements §4 N1, a signing key is authorized for a specific set of effects (its scope). When signing a PAX, the PAX's effect set (from .paideia.effects section) must be a subset of the key's authorized scope. This error indicates a scope mismatch: the key cannot sign this artifact because it lacks authorization for some required effects. Check the key's scope and the artifact's effect declarations."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/Q0901",
              "id": "Q0901",
              "name": "Signing-key scope insufficient",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "the signing key's scope does not subsume the artifact's effect set"
              }
            },
            {
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Phase 3 m6-002 documents this as the canonical hybrid-fallback shape. Operator opt-in is required via --opt-in-hybrid-fallback. See design/security/pq-trust-root.md (phase-3 appendix m6-005)."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://paideia-os.org/diagnostics/Q0902",
              "id": "Q0902",
              "name": "HSM does not support post-quantum signing",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "the configured HSM (YubiHSM2 ≤ firmware 2.6) supports Ed25519 in hardware but not ML-DSA-65; the PQ leg falls back to soft-HSM"
              }
            }
          ],
          "semanticVersion": "0.0.1",
          "version": "0.0.1"
        }
      }
    }
  ],
  "version": "2.1.0"
